  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out (acceptable at MRL 2). One explicitly-flagged gap in model-input uncertainty is documented honestly with wide uncertainty bounds, a dedicated sensitivity analysis, and an offset rationale justifying acceptance.",
