  "sensitivityAnalysisDetail": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/sensitivity/cpb-model-inputs-sa",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sensitivity analysis: blood viscosity and power-law index on hemolysis index",
    "description": "A one-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analysis was performed varying blood dynamic viscosity (±15% around 3.5 mPa·s) and the power-law index n (0.70–0.82) used in the Carreau-Yasuda rheology model. The relative hemolysis index (RHI) exhibited a peak-to-trough spread of 0.18 RHI units across the viscosity range and 0.11 units across the power-law range, with viscosity identified as the dominant driver of wide uncertainty bounds. These bounds remain below the RHI < 1.0 acceptance threshold with margin, supporting acceptance despite the documented input uncertainty gap."
  },
